The UserGuide's Introduction section previously
offered a basic overview of features and
provided generic instructions on downloading
the application.

To provide users with a clearer understanding
and smoother onboarding experience, it's vital
to present a more refined feature overview and
streamlined download instructions.

Let's enhance the feature overview for clarity
and detail. Additionally, refine the download
instructions to ensure users can easily get
started with the application.

Making these changes ensures that users have
a clear initial impression of the tool and
its capabilities, and can effortlessly proceed
with the setup.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update User Guide with Enhanced Icons Desc
commitResults.messageBody:
The UserGuide's Introduction section was primarily
focused on offering a brief glimpse into the
application's features and gave users a generic
roadmap to download and set up the tool.

Understanding that a robust introduction can
greatly influence user perception and usage,
there's an undeniable need to delve deeper
into feature explanations and simplify the
download process.

Aiming to meet these objectives, we should
revamp the feature overview, adding depth
and clarity. Simultaneously, simplifying
the download steps will make the initial
interaction more intuitive for new users.

With these refinements in place, we ensure
that users are not only introduced to the
capabilities of the tool effectively but also
find the setup process seamless and
straightforward.

commitResults.messageTitle: User guide: Add typography box styles for icons
commitResults.messageBody:
The introduction section of the user guide lacked
visual distinction for icons. Introducing styled
typography boxes for icons enhances the clarity
and visual appeal.

Let's update the SCSS file with styles for
typography boxes and apply these styles to icons
in the introduction. Using SCSS allows Jekyll
to compile these styles seamlessly into the CSS.

This approach ensures consistency across the
user guide and provides a cohesive user
experience. Future updates can utilize these
styles for icons and other elements as required.

The PUML diagram for the Delete Command feature
was modified to better represent the current
implementation. Such changes in the diagram
necessitate updates in the associated
documentation to maintain consistency.

Let's refresh the Delete Command section in the
developer guide to align with the updated
diagram. This ensures that developers have
accurate visual and textual information on the
Delete Command's workings.

It's essential to keep the guide synchronized
with changes to provide a reliable reference
for the development team.

commitResults.messageTitle: Clean up developer guide of "stashed changes"
commitResults.messageBody:
The developer guide had accumulated multiple
"stashed changes" messages, which were
distracting and cluttering the documentation.

Let's remove these extraneous messages to
improve the guide's readability and maintain
a cleaner presentation. Keeping the documentation
clear of such distractions ensures that the
focus remains on the content, facilitating a
better experience for the developers.

Furthermore, pruning these messages reduces
potential confusion for new team members who
might misinterpret or be misled by them. It's
essential for our documentation to be as
straightforward and precise as possible.
User guide: Add typography box styles for icons

The developer guide was originally styled with
GFM syntax, which rendered perfectly in GFM.
However, GitHub Pages deployments utilize
kramdown, leading to discrepancies in the
rendering.

Let's modify the Table of Contents and
introduction box styles to ensure compatibility
with kramdown. This change will make certain
that our guide is displayed consistently and
correctly on GitHub Pages.

Adapting to kramdown ensures the documentation
remains professional and accessible to all
users, irrespective of the markdown processor
used in the backend.

commitResults.messageTitle: Adjust icon size to match adjacent text
commitResults.messageBody:
The icons beside the text in the guide boxes
were not proportionally sized, leading to a
visual inconsistency and potential distraction
for the readers.

Let's resize the icons to match the size of the
adjacent text. By ensuring that the icon and
text sizes are harmonious, we enhance the visual
coherence of the documentation.

Such a meticulous attention to detail elevates
the professionalism of the guide and ensures a
seamless reading experience for users.
